headline: Northern Trust Decreases Prime Rate
summary: CHICAGO, October 29, 2025--Northern Trust has decreased its prime rate, effective October 30, 2025.

headline: WSFS Financial Corporation Appoints Michelle Hong to Board of Directors
summary: WILMINGTON, Del., October 29, 2025--WSFS Financial Corporation (Nasdaq: WSFS) today announced that Michelle Hong has been appointed to its Board of Directors, effective December 1, 2025. She will stand for election at the 2026 Annual Meeting of Shareholders.

headline: Canadian Pension Plans Maintain Momentum Through Third Quarter
summary: TORONTO, October 29, 2025--The median plan in the Northern Trust Canada Universe returned 3.6% for the quarter and 4.3% year-to-date for the period ending September 30, 2025.

headline: Clear Street’s Outsourced Trading Team Further Expands
summary: Strengthened by the Firm’s Global Platform Sales Team, Providing Clients Seamless Access to its Expanding Suite of Solutions Brings on Senior Hires from UBS and Northern Trust NEW YORK, Oct. 29, 2025 (GLOBE NEWSWIRE) -- Clear Street (“Clear Street” or the “Company”), a cloud-native financial infrastructure technology firm on a mission to give sophisticated investors access to every asset in every market, today announced the official launch of its outsourced trading business in the UK and Europe.

headline: The 5 Most Interesting Analyst Questions From Northern Trust’s Q3 Earnings Call
summary: Northern Trust’s third quarter results met analyst expectations for revenue and modestly exceeded profit estimates, but the market reacted negatively, reflecting concerns about underlying business trends. Management attributed the quarter’s performance to disciplined expense control, operational productivity programs, and steady organic growth across core business lines.
